# Frontend Development Rule

## 1. TypeScript Standards

- Use strict TypeScript mode with proper type inference
- Define explicit interfaces for all props and API responses
- No `any` types except in legacy code migration or worst case scenario

## 2. Component Standards

- Functional components with proper JSX structure
- Memoization for performance-critical components
- Clear separation of concerns (presentation vs logic)

## 3. Documentation Access

- Always use Context7 MCP tool for accessing official documentation
- Provide latest, up-to-date, non-deprecated code and APIs only
- Reference official docs for Next.js, React, and other technologies

## 4. Error Handling

- Implement proper error boundaries
- User-friendly error messages (never expose internals)
- Graceful degradation for network failures

## 5. Accessibility

- Semantic HTML structure
- ARIA labels for complex components
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
